column14: DESCRIP

AN AUTOMATIC VOLTAGE CONTROL CIRCUIT IN THE EXCITER FAILED, WHICH CAUSED A PROTECTIVE RELAY TO "OPEN" AND TRIP THE TURBINE OFF-LINE:THUS CAUSING AN AUTOMATIC REACTOR SCRAM ON HIGH POWER.TURBINE WAS PLACED ON TURNING GEAR FOR INVESTIGATION/REPAIRS.

AN AUTOMATIC VOLTAGE CONTROL CIRCUIT IN THE EXCITER FAILED AND TRIPPED THE TURBINE OFF-LINE;CAUSING A SCRAM.AFTER REPAIRS AND ATTEMPTING TO RETURN THE UNIT TO SERVICE;HIGH TURBINE VIBRATION WAS NOTICED.THE TURBINE WAS PLACED ON TURNING GEAR FOR REPAIRS.

REMOVED FROM SERVICE TO INVESTIGATE AND REPAIR LEAKAGE FROM MO-7071 AND/OR VPI-303 ON THE POST INCIDENT SYSTEM. AFTER THE UNIT WAS REMOVED FROM SERVICE, THE REACTOR WAS MANUALLY SCRAMMED TO FULLY INSERT THE REMAINING WITHDRAWN CONTROL ROD DRIVES.
